<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-66-0352 </DOCNO><TEXT>Industrial hygiene engineering is a timely topic because engineering controlof occupational health hazards has become a subject of widespread interestin the past few years and is, in fact, a matter of critical importanceand ferment for the occupational health profession. This is because ofOSHA's long standing insistence on the primacy of engineering measuresto control occupational health hazards in preference to personal protectiveequipment or administrative controls, with the result that there is acontinuing demand for industrial hygiene engineering services. The essenceof industrial hygiene engineering is the prevention of occupational diseaseby management of the work environment. It may be accomplished in a numberof ways, each of which is examined as the authors explore the subjectmore fully.</TEXT></DOC>